---
import PageLayout from '../layouts/PageLayout.astro';
---

<PageLayout
  title="Terms of Service | ChinaWebFoundry"
  description="Terms and conditions governing use of the ChinaWebFoundry website and services."
>
  <section class="pt-32 lg:pt-40 pb-24 md:pb-32">
    <div class="mx-auto max-w-[800px] section-padding">
      <p class="text-sm font-semibold uppercase tracking-wider text-[var(--color-brand-orange)] mb-5">
        Legal
      </p>
      <h1 class="text-3xl sm:text-4xl lg:text-[48px] font-medium font-[var(--font-heading)] text-[var(--color-text-dark)] leading-[1.08] mb-6">
        Terms of Service
      </h1>
      <p class="text-sm text-[var(--color-text-muted)] mb-12">
        Last updated: 31 March 2026
      </p>

      <div class="space-y-10 text-base text-[var(--color-text-body)] leading-relaxed">
        <div>
          <h2 class="text-xl font-medium font-[var(--font-heading)] text-[var(--color-text-dark)] mb-3">1. Overview</h2>
          <p>
            These Terms of Service ("Terms") govern your access to and use of the ChinaWebFoundry website (chinawebfoundry.com) and the services we provide. By accessing our website or engaging our services, you agree to be bound by these Terms. If you do not agree, please do not use our website or services.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div>
          <h2 class="text-xl font-medium font-[var(--font-heading)] text-[var(--color-text-dark)] mb-3">2. Services</h2>
          <p>
            ChinaWebFoundry provides WordPress development, hosting, localisation, and digital marketing services for companies operating in or entering the Chinese market. Our services include, but are not limited to, WordPress engineering, China hosting, Baidu SEO, UX/UI design, Chinese content localisation, technical integration, and ongoing maintenance and support.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div>
          <h2 class="text-xl font-medium font-[var(--font-heading)] text-[var(--color-text-dark)] mb-3">3. Website Use</h2>
          <p class="mb-3">When using our website, you agree not to:</p>
          <ul class="list-disc pl-5 space-y-1">
            <li>Violate any applicable laws or regulations</li>
            <li>Send unsolicited promotional or commercial communications</li>
            <li>Attempt to gain unauthorised access to any part of the website or its systems</li>
            <li>Use automated tools to scrape, crawl, or collect data from the website without our prior written permission</li>
            <li>Interfere with or disrupt the website's functionality or security</li>
          </ul>
        </div>

        <div>
          <h2 class="text-xl font-medium font-[var(--font-heading)] text-[var(--color-text-dark)] mb-3">4. Intellectual Property</h2>
          <p>
            All content on this website, including text, graphics, logos, and design elements, is the property of ChinaWebFoundry unless otherwise stated. You may not reproduce, distribute, or create derivative works from our content without prior written consent. Work produced for clients as part of an engagement transfers to the client upon full payment, unless otherwise specified in writing.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div>
          <h2 class="text-xl font-medium font-[var(--font-heading)] text-[var(--color-text-dark)] mb-3">5. Client Responsibilities</h2>
          <p class="mb-3">When engaging our services, clients are expected to:</p>
          <ul class="list-disc pl-5 space-y-1">
            <li>Provide accurate and complete information as required</li>
            <li>Review and approve deliverables in a timely manner</li>
            <li>Ensure that materials provided to us do not infringe any third-party rights</li>
            <li>Pay all agreed fees according to the terms of the engagement</li>
          </ul>
        </div>

        <div>
          <h2 class="text-xl font-medium font-[var(--font-heading)] text-[var(--color-text-dark)] mb-3">6. Payment Terms</h2>
          <p>
            Invoices are due within 30 days of issue unless otherwise agreed in writing. Late payments may incur interest at a rate of 1.5% per month. We reserve the right to suspend services if payment remains outstanding for more than 15 days past the due date.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div>
          <h2 class="text-xl font-medium font-[var(--font-heading)] text-[var(--color-text-dark)] mb-3">7. Confidentiality</h2>
          <p>
            Both parties agree to keep confidential any proprietary or sensitive information disclosed during the engagement. This obligation of confidentiality survives for two years following the termination of the engagement.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div>
          <h2 class="text-xl font-medium font-[var(--font-heading)] text-[var(--color-text-dark)] mb-3">8. Limitation of Liability</h2>
          <p>
            Our services are provided on an "as is" basis. To the fullest extent permitted by law, ChinaWebFoundry makes no warranties, express or implied, regarding the services or website. Our total liability for any claim arising from or related to our services shall not exceed the fees paid by the client for the specific service giving rise to the claim.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div>
          <h2 class="text-xl font-medium font-[var(--font-heading)] text-[var(--color-text-dark)] mb-3">9. Indemnification</h2>
          <p>
            You agree to indemnify and hold ChinaWebFoundry harmless from any claims, damages, losses, or expenses arising from your use of our website or services, your breach of these Terms, or your violation of any third-party rights.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div>
          <h2 class="text-xl font-medium font-[var(--font-heading)] text-[var(--color-text-dark)] mb-3">10. Termination</h2>
          <p>
            Either party may terminate an engagement by providing written notice as specified in the relevant service agreement. We reserve the right to terminate or suspend access to our website at any time, without prior notice, for conduct that we believe violates these Terms or is harmful to other users or our business.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div>
          <h2 class="text-xl font-medium font-[var(--font-heading)] text-[var(--color-text-dark)] mb-3">11. Governing Law</h2>
          <p>
            These Terms are governed by and construed in accordance with the laws of Hong Kong SAR. Any disputes arising from these Terms shall be subject to the exclusive jurisdiction of the courts of Hong Kong.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div>
          <h2 class="text-xl font-medium font-[var(--font-heading)] text-[var(--color-text-dark)] mb-3">12. Changes to These Terms</h2>
          <p>
            We reserve the right to modify these Terms at any time. Changes will be posted on this page with a revised "Last updated" date. Continued use of our website or services after any changes constitutes acceptance of the updated Terms.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div>
          <h2 class="text-xl font-medium font-[var(--font-heading)] text-[var(--color-text-dark)] mb-3">13. Severability</h2>
          <p>
            If any provision of these Terms is found to be invalid or unenforceable, the remaining provisions shall continue in full force and effect.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div>
          <h2 class="text-xl font-medium font-[var(--font-heading)] text-[var(--color-text-dark)] mb-3">14. Contact Us</h2>
          <p>
            If you have any questions about these Terms, please get in touch via our <a href="/contact/" class="text-[var(--color-brand-orange)] hover:underline">contact page</a> or email us at <a href="mailto:hello@chinawebfoundry.com" class="text-[var(--color-brand-orange)] hover:underline">hello@chinawebfoundry.com</a>.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</PageLayout>
